node.text:
Easy to make, these chickpea bites are perfect for meal prep. Served with a creamy avocado dip and fresh veggies, they are perfect for lunchboxes.

INGREDIENTS
1 15 ounce can chickpeas
¾ cup plain breadcrumbs
⅓ cup all purpose flour
1 large egg
Juice of 1 lime
2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon ground cumin
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper
freshly cracked black pepper to taste
Nonstick cooking spray

🖨 INSTRUCTIONS & FULL PRINTABLE RECIPE: https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/chickpea-bites-meal-prep/
 
#ChickpeaBites #StarbucksBox #MealPrep

node.text:
Beef Shawarma is a popular street food especially in the Middle East. Its made with flank steak, wrapped in pita bread with vegetables & tahini sauce.

INGREDIENTS
2 pounds flank steak
1/4 cup olive oil
1/4 cup vinegar
Juice one lemons plus zest
2 tablespoons Shawarma seasoning
4 garlic cloves minced
1 onion sliced

🖨 INSTRUCTIONS & FULL PRINTABLE RECIPE: https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/beef-shawarma/

node.text:
This veggie chickpea burger recipe is simple to make and packed with Mediterranean ingredients like sun-dried tomatoes and feta. Plus I’m sharing more about my @discoverzephyr hood which helps circulate fresh air in my kitchen and keep smoke out!

INGREDIENTS 
¼ red onion
¼ cup fresh parsley
3-4 large garlic cloves
1 teaspoon dried oregano
1 15 ounce can chickpeas, drained and rinsed
½ cup old fashioned or quick oats
¼ cup all purpose flour
½ cup crumbled feta
½ cup sun dried tomatoes drained
2 tablespoons vegetable or olive oil plus more, if needed

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/chickpea-burger/

node.text:
For cookouts, picnics, lunchboxes and anything in between, try this simple macaroni egg salad made with @Stonyfield Organic Whole Milk Yogurt instead of mayonnaise. #sponsored Like mayo, yogurt is tart and tangy and it has a pretty similar texture too which makes it a great swap with less fat and calories.

INGREDIENTS
8 ounces elbow macaroni
Kosher salt to taste
4 large eggs
¾ cup plain whole milk yogurt
½ cup pickles finely chopped
1 tablespoon Dijon mustard
1 tablespoon red wine vinegar
2 teaspoons honey
Freshly ground black pepper to taste
3 stalks celery finely chopped
¼ medium red onion finely chopped
¼ cup minced fresh parsley
 
Full Recipe & Detailed Instructions:
https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/macaroni-egg-salad/

Enjoy these chewy Oatmeal Breakfast Bars in the morning or as a midday snack. They're great for meal prepping in advance and packed with heart healthy oats! They're loved by kids and great for back to school.

🥣 INGREDIENTS
2 cups old-fashioned rolled oats
½ cup cane sugar
1 ½ teaspoons baking powder
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon cinnamon
2 eggs
½ cup almond milk
¼ cup applesauce
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
¼ cup walnuts finely chopped
¼ cup dried cranberries

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/oatmeal-breakfast-bars/

node.text:
Full of fresh flavors, this Air Fryer Greek salmon recipe is a breeze to make. Ready to serve in less than 30 minutes, is healthy, light and so delicious!
INGREDIENTS 
*For the Salmon
4 center cut salmon filets about 1” thick each
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 lemon juiced (about ¼ cup)
2 garlic cloves pressed
½ teaspoon dried oregano
½ teaspoon dried dill
¼ teaspoon red pepper flakes
Salt and pepper to taste
*For the Greek Salad
4 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
2 tablespoons red wine vinegar
½ teaspoon dried oregano
¼ teaspoon salt
¼ teaspoon black pepper
3 vine-ripened tomatoes seeded and chopped
½ English cucumber peeled and chopped
½ small red onion chopped
4 ounces sliced black kalamata olives
Chopped parsley for garnish
2 ounces feta cheese optional

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/air-fryer-greek-salmon/

This is a Lebanese style Beef Kafta recipe that's made with ground beef, parsley, onions and a blend of Middle Eastern spices- perfect on the grill or stove

🧅 INGREDIENTS
¼ cup parsley
1 small yellow onion quartered
1 pound ground beef
2 teaspoons 7 spice
½ teaspoon cumin
½ teaspoon cinnamon
½ teaspoon coriander
⅛ teaspoon cayenne pepper
½ teaspoon salt
¼ teaspoon black pepper to taste

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/beef-kafta/

Ingredients
For the chicken and dressing:
¼ cup plus 3 tablespoons olive oil divided
1 garlic clove minced
1 tablespoon plus two teaspoons red wine vinegar divided
1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoons dried oregano divided
1 teaspoon dried dill
½ teaspoon salt
¼ teaspoon black pepper
1 pound skinless chicken breasts
½ small shallot minced
2 teaspoons Dijon mustard
1 lemon zested and juiced
To assemble:
3-4 cups Romaine lettuce chopped
½ cup crumbled feta
3-4 Persian cucumbers diced
2 plum tomatoes seeded and diced
½ red onion thinly sliced
¼ cup pitted kalamata olives sliced
2 tablespoons fresh chopped dill

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/mediterranean-chicken-salad/

A staple Palestinian meal, Musakhan (also spelled msakhan and musakkhan) is a hearty, festive and very popular recipe all over the Middle East.

INGREDIENTS
2 tablespoons 7 spice divided
2 teaspoons salt divided
3 tablespoons sumac divided
4 whole chicken legs thigh and drumsticks, about 2 and half pounds
¼ cup + 2 tablespoons olive oil
4 medium yellow onions chopped
¼ cup toasted pine nuts
6-8 small flatbreads naan, Greek pita bread or Taboon bread
Lemon slices for serving
Fresh parsley for serving

https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/musakhan/

node.text:
Easy to make, these chickpea bites are perfect for meal prep. Served with a creamy avocado dip and fresh veggies, they are perfect for lunchboxes.

INGREDIENTS
1 15 ounce can chickpeas
¾ cup plain breadcrumbs
⅓ cup all purpose flour
1 large egg
Juice of 1 lime
2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon ground cumin
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper
freshly cracked black pepper to taste
Nonstick cooking spray

🖨 INSTRUCTIONS & FULL PRINTABLE RECIPE: https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/chickpea-bites-meal-prep/
 
#ChickpeaBites #StarbucksBox #MealPrep

node.text:
Beef Shawarma is a popular street food especially in the Middle East. Its made with flank steak, wrapped in pita bread with vegetables & tahini sauce.

INGREDIENTS
2 pounds flank steak
1/4 cup olive oil
1/4 cup vinegar
Juice one lemons plus zest
2 tablespoons Shawarma seasoning
4 garlic cloves minced
1 onion sliced

🖨 INSTRUCTIONS & FULL PRINTABLE RECIPE: https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/beef-shawarma/
